I’m not the most confident in front of a camera.
My Canon camera is two years old but until last week, I’ve never shot a video of myself with it.
It took me 4-5 hours to put together a 35 seconds video (my previous post)!!!! 🙊😂😭
Bruh! I give Videographers, YouTubers and Content Creators their flowers!
It’s not easy! 😅
But I’m proud of myself for trying because I dreaded it so much.
So here’s to trying new things and getting out of our comfort zones! 🥂

I always say my hair is 4Z (if there’s something like that😅) because my coils are extremely packed and dense.
It’s quite dry and I struggle with managing it.
I’ve been in and out of the barber shop because it’s hard to find products that work for my hair type.
I’m gradually accepting that my hair is beautiful and that it just needs more time and care.
I’m happy that @jvnhair | @jvn  made hair products for hair textures like mine.
This set boosts hydration and keeps your hair super moisturized!
Love love it.
And oh, the products smell really good!
Use my discount code, ASHORKS20, for 20% off.

I’m in my late twenties.
I can’t even believe it but life is moving pretty fast.
My friends and I have been having conversations about adulthood and how it’s not everything we imagined or expected.
Highs?
Lows?
It’s a beautiful roller coaster. 
It is quite interesting to know that nobody has it figured out.
We’re just taking it a day at a time.
I am learning to see the beauty in all the chaos. 
Like the sunrise after a dark night, we too can hope for smiles after tough days….

I’m slowly falling in love with my natural hair again.
I was wrong to think that it wasn’t beautiful.
I had compared it to different textures several times and gave myself a million reasons why it was just not for me.
Worst thing I did was to go to hairdressers that didn’t know how to handle my hair type.
It felt like torture.
Well, I know better now and that is why it’s important I use products meant just for my hair type.
@4ubytia was created to make the natural hair journey simpler. 
Their star ingredient is Hemi15 which helps to nourish and repair curls.
The other ingredients?
Aloe Vera, Apple Cider Vinegar, Watermelon, Hibiscus etc?
@4ubytia really did that and I am so in love!
I look forward to my wash days with excitement now. 
Thank you! ❤️
.

Master of Arts in Entrepreneurship for Creatives ✅
.
I started my career as a midwife. 
Prior to that, I was taking pictures in Aburi Girls Senior High, Ghana, with a small digital camera (Fujifilm) my uncle had gifted me for my 16th birthday.
I developed a deep interest in photography and I would take pictures of everything and I still do to this day. 
.
Working as a midwife, I would use my off days to do creative work and freelance for @littletokensfoundation as a photographer ( @eyram.ashorkor ).
I later started @the_ninety4_shop , an online decor shop where I sell decor items for homes and offices.
I explored a lot of creative outlets from hair to makeup to anything creative.
I even wanted to be a chef at a point.😃
In 2021, I couldn’t ignore the creative itch and I was ready to fully commit to it and pursue it professionally.
My time at @columbiachi has been an amazing ride.
Being in a community full of creatives is one I wouldn’t take for granted. 
The creative force is as strong as the wind in Chicago.
If there’s anything I’ve learnt, it’s that as creatives we have the power to change the world with the stories we tell.
We can take the road less traveled and create change. ✨
.
Sash : @sash_by_nuella .
Cap design: @nissiecreatives .
.

the 29th year…🎈
.
in business school, more often than not, you get asked what makes you or your venture unique and i’ve spent the last year building @the.ashe.co with this question always in mind.
.
my younger self wanted to be a pilot or an architect.
my teenage self just wanted to serve.
in my 20s, i just to live creatively and walk in God’s purpose for me.
if you ask me, our passions and experiences have a beautiful way of colliding eventually.
.
life design is still an aspect of creation that fascinates me.
as humans, we are all very different but we compliment each other so well.
our experiences are ours and very unique but someway somehow, they are the answers to problems around us.
.
29 years and everyday i still learn that i will keep evolving.
change is a constant and where ever this new road leads, i will go.
